<!--
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  YVON SKILL TEMPLATE — Adoption A1 (gstack pattern, YVON-native)
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  This template is the single source of the COMPILED skill format.
  The generator (cli/skillgen.js) reads an agent's source files in Teams/
  and fills every {{PLACEHOLDER}} below. Output lands in dist/skills/<agent>/.

  Teams/ is the single source of truth. Generated output is disposable —
  never hand-edit a generated skill; edit the source and regenerate.

  PLACEHOLDER → SOURCE MAP (derived, never invented — Playbook §0.5):
    {{SKILL_NAME}}      ← source SKILL.md frontmatter `name`
    {{AGENT_ID}}        ← source frontmatter `assigned_agent` (id only)
    {{DEPT}}            ← source frontmatter `assigned_agent` (dept part)
    {{VERSION}}         ← 1.0.0 on first generation; generator bumps minor
                          when source_hash changes
    {{TIER}}            ← preamble tier. Default rule:
                            1 = router/index skills
                            2 = advisory/creative (no config, no builds)
                            3 = config-dependent (reads agent config; loud
                                <FILL_IN> detection)
                            4 = build/exec (retrieval + TASK-SPEC slice)
                          Overrides: `tier:` field in source frontmatter wins.
    {{DESCRIPTION}}     ← first sentence of source `## Purpose` + routing
                          hints; ends with "(yvon)" marker
    {{TRIGGERS}}        ← derived from source `## When to Use` phrases +
                          this skill's entries in the agent's
                          operational/skill/<agent>-skill-routing.md
    {{ALLOWED_TOOLS}}   ← operational/tool/<agent>-tool-requirements.md;
                          unknown/<FILL_IN> values pass through as-is —
                          the preamble flags them loudly at runtime
    {{SOURCE_PATH}}     ← repo-relative path of the source SKILL.md
    {{SOURCE_SHA256}}   ← hash of source at generation time (Gate 1 of the
                          harness authenticates generated skill ↔ source)
    {{TIMESTAMP}}       ← generation time (ISO)
    {{PREAMBLE}}        ← tier-matched preamble block from
                          Teams/Shared OS/skills/skill-template/preambles/
                          (Artifact 2)
    {{WHEN_TO_USE}}     ← source `## When to Use` (condensed)
    {{PURPOSE}}         ← source `## Purpose` (condensed)
    {{PROTOCOL}}        ← source `## Structure / Protocol` (verbatim —
                          the load-bearing content, never summarized)
    {{BOUNDARIES}}      ← this skill's handoff rules from the agent's
                          skill-routing file (upstream/downstream skills,
                          precedence when requests match multiple)
    {{OUTPUT_FORMAT}}   ← source `## Output Format` if present, else omitted

  RULES (enforced by generator, not hope):
    - §0.4  No venture/company names anywhere in generated output —
            source provenance frontmatter is the only permitted location.
    - §0.5  Nothing invented: a placeholder with no source data renders as
            an explicit <FILL_IN: what's missing> marker, never a guess.
    - Sections with no source content are OMITTED, not stubbed — generated
      skills stay token-lean (CAOS economy applies to skills themselves).
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-->
---
name: {{SKILL_NAME}}
agent: {{AGENT_ID}}
department: {{DEPT}}
version: {{VERSION}}
tier: {{TIER}}
description: |
  {{DESCRIPTION}}
triggers:
{{TRIGGERS}}
allowed-tools:
{{ALLOWED_TOOLS}}
owns-paths: {{OWNS_PATHS}}
identity: {{IDENTITY}}
provenance:
  source_file: {{SOURCE_PATH}}
  source_hash: {{SOURCE_SHA256}}
  generated: {{TIMESTAMP}}
  generator: cli/skillgen.js
portable: true
---
<!-- AUTO-GENERATED from {{SOURCE_PATH}} — DO NOT EDIT.
     Edit the source in Teams/, then regenerate: node cli/skillgen.js {{AGENT_ID}} -->

## Preamble (run first)

{{PREAMBLE}}

## When to invoke this skill

{{WHEN_TO_USE}}

## Purpose

{{PURPOSE}}

## Protocol

{{PROTOCOL}}

## Boundaries & handoffs

{{BOUNDARIES}}

## Output format

{{OUTPUT_FORMAT}}

## Voice

{{VOICE}}

## Completion (run last)

{{POSTAMBLE}}
